            . I keep the Bird-in-hand, a public house, in Oxford Road. The prisoner came to my house on the 24th of June, about six in the morning, and asked for a pennyworth of purl. He had a bundle with him, which he endeavoured to conceal. I suspecting him, stopped him, and charged a constable with him; and in Tuesday's paper the things were advertised. The things were found upon him.</p>
               <p>The prisoner's defence was, that he found the things near the house.</p>
